/-
This module proves that PSL(2, p) is a simple group for any prime p ≥ 5.
The proof relies on Iwasawa's Lemma (`MulAction.IwasawaStructure.isSimpleGroup`).
We construct an Iwasawa structure for the action of PSL(2, p) on the projective line `Projectivization (ZMod p) (Fin 2 → ZMod p)`.
The subgroups `T(x)` in the Iwasawa structure are defined as conjugates of the subgroup `A_inf` (image of upper unitriangular matrices).
We prove that `T(x)` is abelian, the family `T` is closed under conjugation, and the subgroups `T(x)` generate PSL(2, p).
Combined with the facts that PSL(2, p) is perfect, the action is faithful and primitive, this establishes the simplicity of PSL(2, p).
-/

